Class AppInterfaceCommandFailureResponseException

  • java.lang.Object
    • java.lang.Throwable
      • java.lang.Exception
        • com.seagullsw.appinterface.client.java.AppInterfaceCommandException
          • com.seagullsw.appinterface.client.java.AppInterfaceCommandFailureResponseException
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.io.Serializable

    public class AppInterfaceCommandFailureResponseException
extends AppInterfaceCommandException

    Checked exceptions of type AppInterfaceCommandFailureResponseException are thrown by an AppInterfaceCommand command bean when its executing interface function returns normally, but with some failure code set in the response.

    The bean's AppInterfaceCommand.execute() method is arranged to raise such exceptions as appropriate, at which time the failure code and description can be retrieved with getReturnCode() and getDescription().
